What you need to know:

If not for its absurdity, the befuddled referee’s comical stunt at the Omnisport Stadium during a Group 'F' fixture between Tunisia and Mali would have easily passed off as ingeniousIt got worse after Sikazwe’s gaffe when tournament organisers attempted to get the two teams back on the pitch to play out the three minutes of stoppage timeCaf has since overruled an appeal by Tunisia to have the match replayed and further explained that the disgraced referee suffered sunstroke and had to go to hospital to recover after the match